## Resources

This skill includes example resource directories. Customize or delete as needed:

### scripts/
Executable code (Python/Bash/Node.js/etc.) for deterministic operations.

**When to include:**
- Repeated code patterns that would be rewritten each time
- Operations requiring exact, error-free execution
- Complex algorithms or data processing

**Benefits:**
- Token efficient (scripts can execute without loading into context)
- Deterministic and tested
- Reusable across multiple skill invocations

**Note:** AI Agents may still read scripts for understanding or patching.

### references/
Documentation and reference material loaded into context as needed.

**When to include:**
- Detailed API documentation
- Database schemas
- Comprehensive workflow guides
- Domain knowledge and policies
- Information too lengthy for SKILL.md

**Benefits:**
- Keeps SKILL.md concise
- Progressive disclosure (loaded only when needed)
- Separate concerns (instructions vs reference material)

**Best practice:** For files >10k words, include grep search patterns in SKILL.md.

### assets/
Files used in output generation, not loaded into context.

**When to include:**
- Templates (document templates, boilerplate code)
- Images, icons, logos
- Fonts
- Sample data files

**Benefits:**
- Separates output resources from documentation
- Enables file reuse without context window consumption
- Supports template-based generation

